This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with the detection of malicious domains generated by malware using domain generation algorithms (DGAs). The paper also makes use of machine learning techniques, specifically recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of side information, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) or Software Engineering (cs.SE).
